## 21. What is Local Storage?
Stores data in browser permanently.

```js
localStorage.setItem("name","Azmuddin");

localStorage.getItem("name");
```
## 22. What is Session Storage?
Stores data until browser tab is closed.

```js
sessionStorage.setItem("user","Ali");

## 23. Difference between Local Storage and Session Storage?
| Local Storage      | Session Storage          |
| ------------------ | ------------------------ |
| Permanent          | Temporary                |
| Larger lifetime    | Removed after tab closes |
| Shared across tabs | Tab-specific             |

## 24. What is Cookie?
Cookies store small pieces of data in the browser.

Uses:
* Authentication
* User Preferences
* Session Management

## 25. What is Responsive Design?
Responsive design makes websites adapt to different screen sizes.
Example:
```css
@media(max-width:768px){
   body{
      font-size:14px;
   }
}

